20/02/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- Prime Minister Sali Berisha told a cabinet meeting Tuesday (February 19th) that Albania is establishing a diplomatic representation in Kosovo. 
Berisha said that after consulting with President Bamir Topi, veteran diplomat Islam Lauka has been tapped to serve as Albania's ambassador in Pristina. 
(Albanian Prime Minister website, Balkanweb, Top-Channel, Makfax - 19/02/08)
